gate.creole.ontology.impl
Class AbstractOntologyImpl

java.lang.Object
  gate.util.AbstractFeatureBearer
      gate.creole.AbstractResource
          gate.creole.AbstractLanguageResource
              gate.creole.ontology.impl.AbstractOntologyImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
Ontology, LanguageResource, Resource, FeatureBearer, NameBearer, Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractOntologyImplSesame
public abstract class AbstractOntologyImpl
extends AbstractLanguageResource
implements Ontology

This class provides implementation of most of the methods of Ontology interface. This implementation is based on the OntologyService (a SAIL) that stores data in repository using SESAME.

Author:
Niraj Aswani, Johann Petrak

knownImportURIs

protected Set<String> knownImportURIs
The ontology import URIs that were already processed for this ontology. NOTE: this contains both the URIs from imports and the ontology URIs from loading ontology data in order to prevent that an ontology that was loaded gets again loaded as an import. Having an ontology loaded both normally and as an import will cause things to break in absurd and unpredictable ways!!!

doSetAutoLabel

protected boolean doSetAutoLabel
This field controls whether new ontology entities will have their label set to the entity resource name automatically. The behavior has changed from the old to the new implementation: the old implementation always set the label, the new implementation does not do that for the new LRs. However, to provide better temporary backwards compatibility, the backwards compatibility LR sets this to true and does create the labels automatically.

addMinCardinalityRestriction

public MinCardinalityRestriction addMinCardinalityRestriction(RDFProperty onProperty,
                                                              String minCardinalityValue)
                                                       throws InvalidValueException
Adds a new MinCardinality Restriction to the ontology. It automatically creates a randon anonymous class, which it uses to denote the restriction. The default datatype is set to NonNegativeIntegerNumber

Specified by:
addMinCardinalityRestriction in interface Ontology
Parameters:
onProperty - - Specifies the property for which the restriction is being set.
minCardinalityValue - - generally a numeric number.
Returns:
Throws:

getOResourceByName

public OResource getOResourceByName(String resourceName)
Try to return the only OResource with the given resource name. If there is no such resource return null. If there is more than one OResource where the fragment identifier of the URI matches the given resource name, return an arbitrary one and output a warning.

Specified by:
getOResourceByName in interface Ontology
Parameters:
resourceName -
Returns:
an OResource object that matches the name or null, if none found

getOResourcesByName

public List<OResource> getOResourcesByName(String resourceName)
Find all OResources for the given resource name. These can be OResources with different URI but identical fragment identifier. If the ontology is not OWL-Lite (which is not officially supported by this implementation) this could also be an URI that can be represented by different subtypes of OResource, e.g. an entity which is both an instance and a class (which is possible in OWL-Full).

Specified by:
getOResourcesByName in interface Ontology
Parameters:
resourceName -
Returns:
a list of OResource objects that have the given resource name.

public List<OResource> getAllResources()

getSourceURL

public abstract URL getSourceURL()
Return an URL that is related to the source of the ontology. This needs to be implemented by all implementing LRs so the factory can determine a name based on the source of the ontology. If the ontology is empty or the source otherwise unknown, null can be returned. This is not part of the public ontology API but used internally by the GATE Factory.

Returns:
a URL of the source of the ontology
